1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,091
Third group, those who never surrender.

2
00:00:03,601 --> 00:00:09,331
This group, maybe two or three percent of the total, doesn't let pessimism dictate,

3
00:00:09,440 --> 00:00:14,531
doesn't believe in surrendering to suppressive forces, doesn't believe in crawling.

4
00:00:14,880 --> 00:00:18,611
Instead, these people live and breathe success.

5
00:00:19,041 --> 00:00:22,930
This group is the happiest because it accomplishes the most.

6
00:00:23,281 --> 00:00:29,331
These people become top salesmen, top executives, top leaders in their respective fields.

7
00:00:29,761 --> 00:00:33,811
These people find life stimulating, rewarding, worthwhile.

8
00:00:34,161 --> 00:00:41,890
These people look forward to each new day, each new encounter with other people, as adventures to be lived fully.

9
00:00:42,241 --> 00:00:43,491
Let's be honest.

10
00:00:43,681 --> 00:00:49,331
All of us would like to be in the third group, the one that finds greater success each year,

11
00:00:49,361 --> 00:00:52,290
the one that does things and gets results.

12
00:00:52,801 --> 00:01:00,130
To get and stay in this group, however, we must fight off the suppressive influences of our environment.

13
00:01:00,561 --> 00:01:08,370
To understand how persons in the first and second groups will unwittingly try to hold you back, study this example.

14
00:01:08,961 --> 00:01:17,971
Suppose you tell several of your average friends with the greatest sincerity, someday I'm going to be vice president of this company.

15
00:01:18,401 --> 00:01:19,491
What will happen?

16
00:01:19,601 --> 00:01:24,530
Your friends will probably think you were joking, and if they should believe you mean it,

17
00:01:24,641 --> 00:01:29,410
chances are they will say, you poor guy, you sure have a lot to learn.

18
00:01:29,841 --> 00:01:34,291
Behind your back, they may even question whether you have all your marbles.

19
00:01:35,201 --> 00:01:41,010
Now, assume you repeat the same statement with equal sincerity to the president of your company.

20
00:01:41,121 --> 00:01:42,530
How will he react?

21
00:01:42,801 --> 00:01:45,731
One thing is certain, he will not laugh.

22
00:01:46,081 --> 00:01:51,331
He will look at you intently and ask himself, does this fellow really mean this?

23
00:01:51,841 --> 00:01:54,851
But he will not, we repeat, laugh.

24
00:01:55,041 --> 00:01:58,691
Because big men do not laugh at big ideas.

25
00:01:59,361 --> 00:02:04,291
Or suppose you tell some average people you plan to own an expensive home,

26
00:02:04,401 --> 00:02:07,731
and they may laugh at you because they think it's impossible.

27
00:02:08,001 --> 00:02:13,971
But tell your plan to a person already living in an expensive home, and he won't be surprised.

28
00:02:14,081 --> 00:02:18,130
He knows it isn't impossible because he's already done it.

29
00:02:18,641 --> 00:02:25,331
Remember, people who tell you it cannot be done almost always are unsuccessful people,

30
00:02:25,441 --> 00:02:30,051
are strictly average or mediocre at best in terms of accomplishment.
